Citations
Date:  0/0/1882
Source:  Brighter Britain
Author:  HAY
Vol / Page:  1/151
Edition:
Quote:   ... that malignant thing we call a <i>Kauri-bug ... </i>[FN]. species of <i>Blatta</i> or cockroach, ... called Polyzosteria novaezelandiae ... [152] it is oval in shape, .... up to the size of a crown-piece. it is flat, black, hard and shiny, and resembles a cross between a black-beetle and the woodlouse or slater. it stinks. That is all it does, but it is enough. <.i>ibid.</i> 2/228 i spoke of the mosquito ..., of the sand-fly ..., and of the kauri-bug <i>(Polyzosteria N.Z.). </i>
